The Naira recorded a mixed performance in different segments of the foreign exchange market on Thursday. It weakened 0.07 per cent at the Investors and Exporters (I&E) forex window, having opened at N362.45, and closed at N362.79. Investors traded a total of $208.81 million through the I&E window on Thursday. At the interbank, the Naira/USD spot and SMIS rates remained unchanged at N306.90/$ and N358.51/$ respectively. The local currency exchanged N360/$ at the parallel, remaining unchanged.